Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: "Access Denied" errors when running scripts

Verify AWS credentials are properly configured
Check that simulated environment has necessary permissions
Review IAM policy syntax for errors
Issue: Scripts not finding roles or policies

Ensure you're working in the correct AWS region
Verify role names match exactly (case-sensitive)
Check that resources were created successfully
Issue: CloudTrail events not appearing

CloudTrail has a delay of 5-15 minutes for event delivery
Verify CloudTrail is enabled in your region
Check S3 bucket permissions for log delivery
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated critical security concepts around EC2 instance roles and privilege escalation in AWS. You learned to identify misconfigured roles, exploit excessive permissions, and implement defensive measures. Key takeaways:

Least Privilege: Always grant minimum necessary permissions
Permission Boundaries: Use boundaries to prevent escalation
Monitoring: Enable CloudTrail and regularly audit IAM activities
Trust Policies: Carefully configure role trust relationships
Regular Audits: Continuously review and refine IAM permissions
In production environments, implement these security controls proactively and maintain vigilant monitoring for suspicious activities. Understanding attack vectors is essential for building robust cloud security defenses.
